<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3840] Add sanity checks on Configurations to make sure hbase confs have been loaded</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3840</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A common user error (and even hbase dev error) is to pass a vanilla Hadoop Configuration into HBase methods that expect to see all of the relevant hbase defaults from hbase-default.xml. This often results in NPE or issues locating ZK.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should add a method like HBaseConfiguration.verify(conf) which ensures that the conf has incorporated hbase-default.xml. We can do this by checking for existence of hbase.defaults.for.version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
